17 (2) An assignment of which local government or authority, pursuant to the requirements
18 of this article, will provide each service, the geographic areas of the county in which such
19 services are to be provided, and a description of any services to be provided by any local
20 government to any geographic area outside its geographical boundaries. In the event two
21 or more local governments within the county are assigned responsibility for providing
22 identical services within the same geographic area, the strategy shall include an
23 explanation of such arrangement;
24 (3) A description of the source of the funding for each service identified pursuant to
25 paragraph (2) of this Code section; and
26 (4) An identification of the mechanisms to be utilized to facilitate the implementation of
27 the services and funding responsibilities identified pursuant to paragraphs (2) and (3) of
28 this Code section.; and
29 (5)(A) As used in this paragraph, the term:
30 (i) 'Affected municipality' shall have the same meaning as set forth in Code Section
31 36-70-25.2; and
32 (ii) 'Growth boundary agreement' means an agreement by a county and all
33 municipalities located wholly or partially within such county that outlines and defines
34 future potential growth through annexation for such municipalities.
35 (B) A growth boundary agreement, unless the county and each affected municipality
36 agree in such service delivery strategy to exclude such a growth boundary agreement."
37 SECTION 2.
38 This Act shall become effective on January 1, 2026.
39 SECTION 3.
40 All laws and parts of laws in conflict with this Act are repealed.
